      "content": "okay, i see what you mean about the shift towards the east. but let's look closer at how we portray them. if we are trying to maintain that \"prestige\" and \"timeless\" feel, how do those different groups actually behave differently in these ads? like, is there a difference in the \"vibe\" or personality we should associate with the European demographic versus the Asian or Middle Eastern ones? i want to make sure we aren't just slapping a different face on the same old concept, but actually capturing the essence of what makes each group's version of luxury feel authentic.",
